name: Cavan Sullivan
summary: In a historic moment, 14-year-old Cavan Sullivan made his professional debut for the Philadelphia Union in Major League Soccer, becoming the youngest player in any major professional sports league in North America. Sullivan, hailed as a "generational talent," impressed with his skills and composure, setting a new record previously held by Freddy Adu. The Union's 5-1 victory over the New England Revolution marked a significant milestone for Sullivan, who became the youngest player ever to appear in an MLS game, breaking a record that had stood for over two decades.

name: Nasdaq
summary: US stock markets experienced a downturn on July 17, 2024, with the Nasdaq and S&P 500 indices closing sharply lower. Semiconductor stocks and megacap companies were major contributors to the decline. The Nasdaq 100 Index had its worst day in 11 months, losing significant value due to a plunge in chipmaker stocks prompted by China's export restrictions. The Nasdaq also slid following a shift away from technology stocks towards small-cap companies. The Dow Jones Industrial Average, however, extended its rally. Concerns about a potential Nasdaq crash have emerged due to the sharp drop in the technology sector.

summary: Multiple sources are reporting significant concerns within the Democratic Party about President Joe Biden's re-election prospects. An AP-NORC poll indicates that nearly two-thirds of Democrats favor Biden withdrawing from the race. Senior party members, including Rep. Schiff and Rep. Pelosi, have privately expressed concerns about Biden's ability to defeat former President Trump. Former President Obama has shared that he believes Biden's path to victory has narrowed. Biden has reportedly grown more receptive to discussions about stepping aside. Prominent voices, such as Ashley Judd, are publicly urging Biden to withdraw, citing the critical need to defeat Trump. Concerns about Biden's viability are also reflected in dwindling donor support. Some top Democrats now believe that Biden is likely to exit the race.
